results.name: Fixed points of A109812.
comment: No further fixed point was found up to A109812(10000000).

The permutation A109812 has regions with smaller amplitude of A109812(n)-n in relative proximity to values of A305370 (Index of 2^n in A109812), this causes higher probability of fixed points in these regions. The permutation A109812 has only weak selfsimilarity and increases its complexity with each interval 2^m..2^(m+1), by this increasing complexity it will be extremely difficult to find any rules and proofs regarding fixed points.
link: Thomas Scheuerle, MATLAB program for calculation of this sequence.
Thomas Scheuerle, Graph of A109812(n)-n shows periodic regions of higher probability for fixed points.
